<DOC><DOCNO> WSJ861222-0130 </DOCNO><HL> Tele-Communications Purchase</HL><DD> 12/22/86</DD><SO> WALL STREET JOURNAL (J)</SO><IN> TCOMA UACIATENDER OFFERS, MERGERS, ACQUISITIONS (TNM)TELECOMMUNICATIONS, BROADCASTING, TELEPHONE, TELEGRAPH (TEL) </IN><DATELINE> DENVER  </DATELINE><TEXT>   Tele-Communications Inc. said it completed the planned acquisition of a 55% stake in United Artists Communications Inc.    Tele-Communications is the nation's largest cable-TV concern. United Artists, San Francisco, also has interests in cable television; the company isn't related to the movie studio of that name.    Tele-Communications acquired the stake from Marshall Naify and Robert A. Naify and their family for $150 million cash and $268 million face amount of convertible notes. The notes are convertible into 15 million Tele-Communications Class A common shares. </TEXT></DOC>